## Example 4 — Determine if a Point Is in the Solution Region

Is the point $(2, 3)$ in the solution region of the system?

$$x + y \leq 7$$

$$2x - y \geq 1$$

$$x \geq 0$$

### Step 1: Test Inequality 1

$$2 + 3 \leq 7 \implies 5 \leq 7 \quad \text{TRUE} \checkmark$$

### Step 2: Test Inequality 2

$$2(2) - 3 \geq 1 \implies 4 - 3 \geq 1 \implies 1 \geq 1 \quad \text{TRUE} \checkmark$$

### Step 3: Test Inequality 3

$$2 \geq 0 \quad \text{TRUE} \checkmark$$

### Step 4: Conclusion

$(2, 3)$ satisfies all three inequalities. It is **in the solution region**.

### Step 5: Test a Counterexample

Test $(5, 5)$: Inequality 1: $5 + 5 = 10 \leq 7$ ✗. Not in the region.

✅ Answer: **Yes**, $(2, 3)$ is in the solution region — it satisfies all three inequalities.

